</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="58FF2A5EFFBEFFD10DCFBB79C1C7FB29" box="[755,898,1128,1154]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="25.[160,225,1354,1377]" captionTargetBox="[165,1151,147,1319]" captionTargetId="figure-24@25.[163,1152,142,1323]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 5. Diversity of Photurinae fireflies of the Serrados Órgãos.A –Bicellonycha albilatera, B – Bicellonycha tenuicornis, C – Photuris velox, D – Photuris elliptica, E – Photuris femoralis (modified from Souto et al. 2019), F – Photuris lugubris, G – Pyrogaster moestus, H – Pyrogaster lunifer, I – Pyrogaster vestitus, J – Pyrogaster elongatior, K – Pyrogaster aureus, L – Pyrogaster angustatus, M – Pyrogaster nigrolineatus, N – Pyrogaster telephorinus, O – Pyrogaster margipallens, P – Pyrogaster atrocinctus, Q – Pyrogaster coxalis. Scale bar:2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5021078" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5021078/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="302">Figure 5 M</figureCitation>
